00:14:39,667 --> 00:14:40,733
<i>- Mom! Mom!
- Manuel!</i>

262
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,200
<i> Manuel!</i>

263
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,767
<i> Manuel!</i>

264
00:14:50,967 --> 00:14:52,300
If you didn't leave me...

265
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:55,033
this wouldn't have happened
to you.

266
00:14:58,233 --> 00:15:00,167
If you didn't leave me,

267
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,067
then you wouldn't be lying
on this hospital bed.

268
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:08,367
Eighteen years, Manuel.

269
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,867
Eighteen years.

270
00:15:13,067 --> 00:15:14,800
I tried to love you.

271
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,967
But you...

272
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:24,933
Not once have I felt loved
by you.

273
00:15:27,367 --> 00:15:30,167
After everything
that we've been through,

274
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,933
you should have known by now.

275
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,433
You should have accepted the
fact...

276
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:40,767
that you can never leave me just
like that.

277
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,133
Look...

278
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:51,033
fate has brought you back to me.

279
00:15:54,867 --> 00:15:56,700
So now there's nothing
you can do.

280
00:15:58,233 --> 00:15:59,433
You have no choice.

281
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:03,200
Because you will end up with me.

282
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,000
Mom, you're here right on time,

283
00:16:17,533 --> 00:16:21,400
I just finished the marketing
plan for Sisig ni Bunso.

284
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:22,667
But of course I made it based

285
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,600
on what you and Uncle Noah
discussed with me.

286
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,567
Did you call Jessica?

287
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:32,900
Who's Jessica?

288
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,333
Are you playing dumb right now?

289
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,700
Or you just didn't know,

290
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:42,267
what Hazel and Manuel's
daughter's name is.

291
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:44,700
I know what you've done.

292
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:46,600
Don't try to deny it.

293
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:47,967
I talked to Jessica.

294
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,733
I'm not gonna deny it.

295
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:52,167
I'm proud of what I've done.

296
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,533
I should have done that
a long time ago

297
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,433
Andrea, I didn't raise you
to be rude!

298
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,800
I wasn't rude to her!

299
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:02,600
I just told her
what she needed to know

300
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:04,267
so she could tell her parents.

301
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,067
So that they all come
to their senses!

302
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:08,967
What you did is wrong!

303
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:12,033
You dragged an innocent person
into this!

304
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:15,933
Mom, I didn't know
she was messing

305
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:17,200
with her dad's phone.

306
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:20,433
And why does it seem like
you're mad at me?

307
00:17:21,867 --> 00:17:25,067
I'm just trying to avenge you.

308
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:27,700
What she did is wrong!

309
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:28,967
Look at what's happening,

310
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,333
even Coleen is getting
affected by it.

311
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:32,467
She's getting bullied at school
because of that video!

312
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:35,100
Mom! I'm just fighting
for our family!

313
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:36,267
Especially you!

314
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,533
You can't just pick a fight
with them.

315
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:45,400
Without even knowing
what they're going through.

316
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:48,767
What are they going through?

317
00:17:49,133 --> 00:17:50,333
Come on, Mom!

318
00:17:50,867 --> 00:17:52,833
Did she tell you sob stories?
She's playing a victim?

319
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:55,000
Is that why?

320
00:17:56,167 --> 00:17:58,700
You're picking a fight
at the wrong time.

321
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:02,500
Because Manuel got shot.

322
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,167
Your dad is in a critical
condition.

323
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:12,600
I don't care about him.

324
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,767
He hasn't been part of
our family for a long time now.

325
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,433
Andrea, sweetie.

326
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:20,900
We appreciate what you did.

327
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:25,200
I appreciate that you want
to protect our family.

328
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:29,333
I'm grateful to you
for fighting for me.

329
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:33,000
But there's another way
to do it.

330
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:34,333
You don't need to fight
with them.

331
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:35,867
To be rude...

332
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,567
especially to those who are
innocent.

333
00:18:37,967 --> 00:18:40,667
What did she say?
What did Jessica tell you?

334
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:41,733
What else?

335
00:18:42,067 --> 00:18:43,333
Was she rude?

336
00:18:44,233 --> 00:18:47,700
She begged me not
to involve Manuel...

337
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:50,333
in our anger toward Hazel.

338
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:54,833
Sweetie, I know we've talked
about this already.

339
00:18:55,833 --> 00:19:00,533
I think it's better
that we move on.

340
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:06,933
Let's stay out
of their family's business.

341
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:08,967
Don't call them again.

342
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,000
That's enough.

343
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,600
And one more thing,

344
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,800
Hazel is the kind of person

345
00:19:22,633 --> 00:19:27,300
who enjoys it
when we react to what she does.

346
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:32,133
It makes her mad
when we ignore them.

347
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:34,700
So just let it go.

348
00:19:35,367 --> 00:19:36,833
It'd be better to let it go
than become a bad person

349
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:38,267
because of her.

350
00:19:55,567 --> 00:19:57,200
<i> You all are shameless!</i>

351
00:19:57,333 --> 00:20:01,133
<i>For Dad's sake, we don't need
negativity right now.</i>

352
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:04,033
<i> I don't care about your dad.</i>

353
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:15,600
Dad...

354
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:17,967
I wish you could hear me, Dad.

355
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:21,333
You need to get well soon.

356
00:20:24,033 --> 00:20:27,033
I can't stand seeing you
like this, Dad.

357
00:20:30,033 --> 00:20:35,233
I admit, I'm feeling selfish
right now, Dad.

358
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:40,300
I need you, Dad.

359
00:20:41,567 --> 00:20:43,800
I need you.

360
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,467
<i> Mommy, you're so mean!</i>

361
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:47,867
<i> What?</i>

362
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:50,733
<i>-You're too much!
-That's enough!</i>

363
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:52,633
<i>We're not done talking, Jessica!</i>

364
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:54,400
<i>-You can't talk back to me!
- Hazel, that's enough.</i>

365
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:56,000
<i> No! Why? Stay out of this!</i>

366
00:20:56,133 --> 00:20:57,933
<i>You're enabling her.
That's why she's rebelling!</i>

367
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:01,467
<i> You're a bastard, Manuel!</i>

368
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:04,033
<i> Mom, what did you do to him?</i>

369
00:21:04,167 --> 00:21:05,600
<i> I didn't mean to do it</i>

370
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:08,367
<i> Hazel, I'm so tired of this!</i>

371
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:11,367
<i>You know what? It's better
we go our separate ways.</i>

372
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,267
<i> Dad, I'm coming with you.</i>

373
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:15,633
<i>No! What do you mean
you're coming with him?</i>

374
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:17,200
<i>- You stay here, Jessica!
- No!</i>

375
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:19,467
<i>- You stay...
- No, I wanna be with Dad.</i>

376
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:29,033
Dad, you have to wake up
for me.

377
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:31,167
Please, Dad.

378
00:21:33,067 --> 00:21:35,800
Please, Dad. I can't bear
to be alone, Dad.

379
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:41,033
You're the only person
I can count on.

380
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:48,533
Dad, please wake up for me.

381
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,200
I need you.

382
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:54,533
I need you, Dad.

383
00:21:55,567 --> 00:21:57,767
I love you so much.

384
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:21,067
After everything
we've been through...

385
00:22:22,867 --> 00:22:25,067
before Manuel had a new family,

386
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:32,567
I never wished for him
to be at death's door.

387
00:22:33,533 --> 00:22:36,600
I never wish him harm

388
00:22:38,167 --> 00:22:39,933
for me to forgive him.

389
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,300
God...

390
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:48,000
please save him.

391
00:22:51,867 --> 00:22:54,333
and please heal Manuel.

392
00:22:59,067 --> 00:23:00,067
Dad.

393
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:08,900
Dad.

394
00:23:09,367 --> 00:23:11,667
Dad, you're awake! Dad!

395
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:14,100
Dad, you're awake!

396
00:23:14,733 --> 00:23:17,467
Dad, you're finally awake, Dad!

397
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,333
Dad, I love you, Dad.

398
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:26,067
I love you.

399
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:31,033
Honestly,

400
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:33,967
I'm at peace and I'm happy now.

401
00:23:35,133 --> 00:23:36,500
With my children...

402
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:41,867
with Jeffrey, Andrea,
Coleen...

403
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:44,600
and Noah.

404
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:51,833
I pray that Manuel will have a
peaceful and happy life too...

405
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,600
With Hazel and Jessica.

406
00:23:56,600 --> 00:24:01,467
Please take all the anger
in my heart.

407
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:05,100
In all our hearts...

408
00:24:05,233 --> 00:24:07,267
heal us slowly...

409
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,633
until we are able
to forgive them.

410
00:24:29,867 --> 00:24:32,500
Okay, Sir. We're gonna do
a little bit of tests.

411
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,300
Do you feel something from here?

412
00:24:39,767 --> 00:24:40,567
How about here?

413
00:24:41,967 --> 00:24:43,600
- No.
- How about here?

414
00:24:45,533 --> 00:24:47,933
- No.
- I'll go down. Here?

415
00:24:49,233 --> 00:24:49,967
Nothing?

416
00:24:50,767 --> 00:24:51,667
How about here?

417
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:55,333
We're going to do another test.

418
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:00,367
Do you feel something from here?

419
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:02,967
And here?

420
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:04,933
No.

421
00:25:06,467 --> 00:25:07,333
How about here?

422
00:25:08,767 --> 00:25:10,800
- No.
-Do you feel any down here?

423
00:25:11,267 --> 00:25:11,900
No.

424
00:25:12,267 --> 00:25:13,033
How about here?

425
00:25:13,867 --> 00:25:14,667
Yes.

426
00:25:20,067 --> 00:25:22,200
Okay, can you rate it
from one to five?

427
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:25,167
Five being the most
and zero to nothing.

428
00:25:27,433 --> 00:25:28,200
One.

429
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:37,367
Can you try to curl your toes?

430
00:25:57,500 --> 00:26:00,200
Hazel, what damage
is the doctor talking about?

431
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:02,700
Although there's no
official diagnosis yet,

432
00:26:02,833 --> 00:26:06,467
I have a strong feeling that
you had a spinal cord injury.

433
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,067
There's a possibility that...

434
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,833
you will get paralyzed
from the waist down.

435
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,233
The interview will push through.

436
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:14,133
And our engagement.

437
00:26:14,267 --> 00:26:16,033
I think that's more
than enough to cover,

438
00:26:16,167 --> 00:26:17,800
all your viral issues.

439
00:26:19,767 --> 00:26:20,600
Who's that?

440
00:26:22,333 --> 00:26:23,600
Why don't you answer it?
Who's calling?

441
00:26:23,733 --> 00:26:25,733
It's Ava, Mom.
I'll talk to her.

442
00:26:25,867 --> 00:26:27,533
How is your dad?

443
00:26:27,667 --> 00:26:29,967
He woke up after the surgery.

444
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:30,967
They're just monitoring

445
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:33,433
how severe the effect
on him will be.

446
00:26:33,567 --> 00:26:34,333
Jessica!
